<paragraph id="E53EDF7D5617FF90FF5FFF1EFA22F867" blockId="12.[151,1437,1545,2035]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="D7F5036F5617FF90FF5FFF1EFD5DF9B7" bold="true" box="[151,866,1545,1571]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">Erroneous geographical record to Neotropical Region.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="2281A4FE5617FF90FCA3FF1EFA9EF9B6" box="[875,1185,1545,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Elaphropeza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ciliatocosta">
<emphasis id="D7F5036F5617FF90FCA3FF1EFA9EF9B6" box="[875,1185,1545,1570]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">Elaphropeza ciliatocosta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<collectingCountry id="9D969FED5617FF90FF5FFF27FF3DF9DE" box="[151,258,1584,1610]" name="Australia" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">Australia</collectingCountry>
(Brisbane), and 
<bibRefCitation id="8110A28C5617FF90FE0DFF27FC62F9DE" author="Bezzi" box="[453,605,1584,1610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="45" refString="Bezzi, M. (1909) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der sudamerikanischen Dipterenfauna auf Grund der Sammelergebnisse einer Reise in Chile, Peru und Bolivia, ausgefuhrt in den Jahren 1902 - 1904 von W. Schnuse. Fam. Empididae. Nova Acta Academiae Caesareae Leopoldino-Carolinae Germanicae Naturae Curiosorum, Halle, 91, n. 3, 297 - 406." type="journal article" year="1909">
Bezzi (
<number id="5349CD5A5617FF90FDD0FF27FC6AF9DE" box="[536,597,1584,1610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44" value="1909.0">1909</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
registered this species in 
<collectingCountry id="9D969FED5617FF90FC42FF27FDDFF9DE" box="[906,992,1584,1610]" name="Bolivia" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
(Maipiri). 
<bibRefCitation id="8110A28C5617FF90FBAAFF27FB3BF9DE" author="Rafael" box="[1122,1284,1584,1610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="46" refString="Rafael, J. A. (1995) Revisao das especies Neotropicais de Empididae (Diptera) descritas por Mario Bezzi. II. Tachydromiinae. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 39, 733 - 739." type="journal article" year="1995">
Rafael (
<number id="5349CD5A5617FF90FB76FF27FAC4F9DE" box="[1214,1275,1584,1610]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
re-described this species based on Bezzi’s Bolivian exemplar since the 
<typeStatus id="3A3A61DF5617FF90FC85FF41FD8BF9E4" box="[845,948,1622,1648]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">holotype</typeStatus>
from 
<collectingCountry id="9D969FED5617FF90FC36FF41FA55F9E4" box="[1022,1130,1622,1648]" name="Australia" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">Australia</collectingCountry>
was destroyed in 
<number id="5349CD5A5617FF90FA8BFF41FB41F9E4" box="[1347,1406,1622,1648]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44" value="1956.0">1956</number>
at the Hungarian Natural History Museum (
<bibRefCitation id="8110A28C5617FF90FD6BFF6AFD02F903" author="Smith" box="[675,829,1661,1687]" pageId="12" pageNumber="46" refString="Smith, K. G. V. (1961) On the genus Macrostomus Wiedemann (Diptera: Empididae) with notes on the included species and new synonymy. Proceedings of the Royal Entomological Society of London, (B) 30 (3 - 4), 53 - 56." type="journal article" year="1961">
Smith 
<number id="5349CD5A5617FF90FD31FF6AFD02F903" box="[761,829,1661,1687]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44" value="1961.0">1961</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). However, in the same paper, Rafael raises the possibility of the Bolivian exemplar analysed by him was different from that described from 
<collectingCountry id="9D969FED5617FF90FB1BFFB3FB00F92A" box="[1235,1343,1700,1726]" name="Australia" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8110A28C5617FF90FA86FFB3FF2AF970" author="Rafael" pageId="12" pageNumber="46" refString="Rafael, J. A. (1995) Revisao das especies Neotropicais de Empididae (Diptera) descritas por Mario Bezzi. II. Tachydromiinae. Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 39, 733 - 739." type="journal article" year="1995">
Rafael 
<number id="5349CD5A5617FF90FF5FFFDDFEE8F970" box="[151,215,1738,1764]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44" value="1995.0">1995</number>
: 
<number id="5349CD5A5617FF90FF2BFFDDFF2AF970" box="[227,277,1738,1764]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44" value="737.0">737</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). The Bolivian specimen agrees with the Australian 
<typeStatus id="3A3A61DF5617FF90FC46FFDDFDFDF970" box="[910,962,1738,1764]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">type</typeStatus>
description on the basis of color of the anterior region of the scutum and number of bristles on the hind tibia, but differ by having a dark postpedicel, black posterior region on scutum and black hind tibia. So, we believe the Bolivian identification was an error on Bezzi’s part and this is actually an undescribed species, and we exclude this Bolivian record from its geographical record. The Bolivian exemplar is quite damaged (head, all legs and left wing missing, scutum damaged, right wing in slide) and, although the abdomen with male terminalia is in a microvial, we prefer not to describe this new species at this time and wait for more exemplars to be obtained. A revision of Australian species is needed, at which time a 
<typeStatus id="3A3A61DF5617FF90FDE2FECEFCB8F867" box="[554,647,2009,2035]" pageId="12" pageNumber="44">neotype</typeStatus>
for this species can be designated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
